    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, rinse the <strong>white long grain rice</strong> until the water runs clear</p><p>Heat a pot with a matching lid over a medium heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, the <strong>sultanas </strong>and<strong> </strong>a pinch of<strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Once the butter has melted, add the<strong> rice </strong>with 225ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
